@page "/about"

<PageTitle>FiscalFox — About</PageTitle>

<h1>About FiscalFox</h1>

<div class="card prose">
    <p>
        <strong>FiscalFox</strong> is a self-hosted personal finance &amp; investment tracker.
        You own your data: it runs entirely on your machine against your own MySQL database,
        with no paid market-data API and no cloud dependency.
    </p>

    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>FiscalFox.Api</strong> — ASP.NET Core (C#) Web API with EF Core over MySQL.</li>
        <li><strong>FiscalFox.Analytics</strong> — a pure <strong>F#</strong> library for returns, risk and rebalancing, covered by FsCheck property tests.</li>
        <li><strong>FiscalFox.Web</strong> — this Blazor Server UI.</li>
        <li><strong>FiscalFox.Domain</strong> — shared entities and DTOs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The analytics engine</h2>
    <p>All the quantitative math lives in F# as small, pure functions:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Simple &amp; log returns, cumulative wealth index, CAGR.</li>
        <li>Volatility (annualized), maximum drawdown, historical Value-at-Risk, Sharpe ratio.</li>
        <li>Target-weight rebalancing that turns your allocation drift into concrete buy/sell trades.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">
        Prices are cached open data (Stooq / Yahoo-style daily CSVs) shipped with the repo and
        regenerable via <code>data/generate_prices.py</code>. Nothing here requires a paid key.
    </p>
</div>
